SIMPLE: unfold
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unfold
<hw>Un*fold"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>unfealdan</ets>. See 1st <er>Un-</er>, and <er>Fold</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To open the folds of; to expand; to
spread out; <as>as, to <ex>unfold</ex> a tablecloth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Unfold</qex> thy forehead gathered into frowns.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To open, as anything covered or close; to lay open
to view or contemplation; to bring out in all the details, or by
successive development; to display; to disclose; to reveal; to
elucidate; to explain; <as>as, to <ex>unfold</ex> one's designs; to
<ex>unfold</ex> the principles of a science</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Unfold</qex> the passion of my love.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To release from a fold or pen; <as>as, to
<ex>unfold</ex> sheep</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unfold</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unfold
<hw>Un*fold"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To open; to expand; to become
disclosed or developed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wind blows cold⟦br⟧
While the morning doth <qex>unfold</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Fletcher.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unfolder</ent>⟦br⟧
